obo:RO_0002333  a  owl:ObjectProperty .

gomodel:SYNGO_2880  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig.1: \"Dynamin isoform-specific association with Shank/ProSAP proteins and mapping of the binding sites via the yeast two-hybrid assay\"\n\nFig.2: \"Co-immunoprecipitation of dynamin and Shank in COS7 cells\"\n- \"...t dynamin-2 co-immunoprecipitates Shank2 more efficiently than does dynamin-1. Both dynamin isoforms co-immunoprecipitated Myc-tagged Shank1 (Fig. 2b), and, again, overexpressed dynamin-2 performed better than dynamin-1.\"\n\nFig.3: \"Dynamin-2 interacts directly with the Shank/ProSAP family members\"\n- \"To ascertain whether the interaction between dynamin-2 and the Shank family is, indeed, direct, a GST fusion protein containing the region of Shank2 corresponding to the initially identified prey fragment was tested for its ability to bind purified dynamin-2. Clear binding by the GST-Shank2 fusion protein, but not by GST alone, was observed (Fig. 3a).\"\n\nFig.4: \"Immunofluorescence microscopy of dynamin isoforms in hippocampal neurons\"\n- \"Immunofluorescence microscopy of cultured hippocampal neurons revealed punctate staining along dendrites with both the dynamin-2 and dynamin-1b carboxyl-terminal isoform-specific antibodies (Fig. 4). The dynamin-2 staining exhibited clear co-localization with the synaptic marker synaptophysin (Fig. 4).\"\n\nFig.5: \"Specific association of dynamin-2 with postsynaptic densities\"\n- \"Both dynamin-1 and -2 isoforms were found in the synaptosomal fraction. However, dynamin-2 was clearly found in the purified PSD fraction, whereas dynamin-1 was present at low to undetectable amounts (Fig. 5).\"\n\nFig.6: \"Co-expression of PSD proteins\"\n- \"However, triple expression of dynamin-2 with both GKAP1a/SAPAP and Shank1a/ProSAP2 resulted in significant co-localization of the three proteins into clusters that were reminiscent of those formed by overexpressing PSD95 and Shaker K+ channels in COS cells (Fig. 6 and Ref. 53).\". Experimental description: - \"Subcellular Fractionation of Rat Brain Tissue\"\n- \"Rat hippocampal neuronal cultures were prepared from 18-19-day-old rat embryos...\"\n- Species of overexpressed protein is not stated in the paper." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0593-3443" ;
        dc:date           "2018-03-13" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_2880" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

